Everyone is invited to the Bay Area Methods Meeting (BAMM) which will
take place at UC Berkeley on Friday, March 2nd.  

SCHEDULE

11:30-1:00 Lunch

1:00-2:30  Donald Rubin (Harvard): "Validly Estimating True Dose-Response When Only Treatment versus Control is Randomized"
2:45-4:15  Walter Mebane (Cornell): "Election Forensics: A Digit-based Test for Election Manipulations"
4:30-6:00  Simon Jackman (Stanford): "The Social Desirability of Belief in God."

6:15       Dinner

All events will take place at the Berkeley Faculty Club
(http://www.berkeleyfacultyclub.com).  All presentations will be given
in the Howard Room, and lunch and dinner will be served in the Seaborg
Room.  If you plan to attend, please RSVP to Lyn Civitello
<lynciv@berkeley.edu>

This will be the first of what we hope will become an annual meeting
rotating between Stanford, UC Davis and UC Berkeley.

Cheers,
Jas.

